{"id":572923093,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2 years, 2 months","timestamp":1634519292,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"80 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/572923093/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"14.4 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def addTwoNumbers(self, l1: ListNode, l2: ListNode) -> ListNode:\n        # first, convert both lists to ints\n        l1int = 0\n        l2int = 0\n        i = 0\n        while not (l1 == None and l2 == None):\n            if l1 != None:\n                l1int += l1.val*(10**i)\n                l1 = l1.next\n            if l2 != None:\n                l2int += l2.val*(10**i)\n                l2 = l2.next\n            i += 1\n\n        # get result, then convert back to linked list\n        resultint = l1int + l2int\n        result = ListNode()\n        resultit = result\n        while True:\n            resultit.val = resultint % 10\n\n            resultint //= 10\n            if resultint > 0:\n                resultit.next = ListNode()\n                resultit = resultit.next\n            else: break\n\n        return result","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
